    "Although GRU network has simpler structure comparing to LSTM networks, its internal structure is more complicated than the normal RNN.",
    "GRU has one gate less than LSTM, this reduces the matrix multiplication, and consequently, it can save a lot of time without impacting its performance [21,22].",
    "The structure of GRU block is shown in Fig. 2.",
    "GRU's are able to solve the vanishing gradient problem by using an update gate and a reset gate.",
    "The update gate handles information that flows into memory, and the reset gate controls the information that flows out of memory."
